com.serena.dmclient.api
Interface DimensionsObjectFactory

public interface DimensionsObjectFactory

This interface is used to create Dimensions CM objects. There are methods for creating new Dimensions CM objects in the repository, and for finding existing Dimensions CM objects and returning them as DimensionsObject instances.

setCurrentProject

void setCurrentProject(java.lang.String projectName,
                       boolean isDefault,
                       java.lang.String directory,
                       java.lang.String defaultRequest,
                       java.lang.String defaultBranch,
                       boolean reset)
Sets the current project for the current user.

Parameters:
projectName - the name of the project to be switched to, qualified with a product name, for example PAYROLL:WS_DEV_WIN.
isDefault - Whether the project should be the default project from now on.
directory - The local user directory that should be used for this project.
defaultRequest - ID of request to be set as default request on the project. If an empty String is supplied, any existing default request will be removed from the project. If null is supplied, the default request will not be changed at all.
defaultBranch - Id of branch to be set as default branch on the project. If an empty String is supplied, any existing default branch will be removed from the project. If null is supplied, the default branch will not be changed at all.
reset - If false, this method doesn't change to the given project, but only sets the default request and/or branch on the given project
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if the current project could not be set to the specified value.
java.lang.NullPointerException - if projectName is null.
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if projectName is not of the form PRODUCT_NAME:PROJECT_NAME

copyDurules

boolean copyDurules(java.lang.String ruleid,
                    java.lang.Object projectId,
                    java.lang.String partId)
Copies the durules default ruleset for ruleid to the new projectId. Use of this method is not recommended.

Parameters:
ruleid - the ruleid e.g $$ecl or $$mrg.
projectId - is either a String identifier e.g "54321" - arbitrary string or is a Project in which case the internal unique identifier is used as a String.
partId - optional part ID to set in the new rules.
Returns:
success or failure - fails if projectId "0" or ruleset exists
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if either of the ruleid or projectId parameters is null.
DimensionsRuntimeException - if there was a general problem copying the rulesets

queryDurules

ItemRevisionDetails[] queryDurules(java.lang.String ruleid,
                                   java.lang.String projectId,
                                   java.lang.String productId,
                                   java.lang.String worksetId,
                                   java.lang.String projectRoot,
                                   java.lang.String contextRoot,
                                   java.lang.String[] filenames)
Deprecated. use Ex versions Queries Upload rules for array of filenames.

Parameters:
ruleid - the ruleid e.g $$ecl or $$mrg
projectId - an IDE project identifier e.g "54321" - arbitrary string.
productId - optional product name.
worksetId - Project spec e.g PROD:ID.
projectRoot - the root of the project.
contextRoot - the context root (optional).
filenames - array of filenames to get details for
Returns:
an array of ItemRevisionDetail instances containing values for the following parameters for item creation or null if no rule found to upload or excluded. Note - project filename and userfilename are not filled in. $COMMENT $DESCRIPTION X $DIRPATH X $FILENAME $FORMAT $ITEM_ID $LIB_FILENAME $OWNING_PART_ID $OWNING_PART_PCS $OWNING_PART_VARIANT $PRODUCT_ID X $REVISION X $STATUS $TYPE $VARIANT $WSPATH
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if the ruleid, projectId, worksetId or projectRoot parameters are null.
DimensionsRuntimeException - if there was a general problem querying the rulesets.

queryDurulesEx

UploadItemDetails[] queryDurulesEx(java.lang.String ruleid,
                                   java.lang.String projectId,
                                   java.lang.String productId,
                                   java.lang.String worksetId,
                                   java.lang.String projectRoot,
                                   java.lang.String contextRoot,
                                   java.lang.String[] filenames)
Queries server Upload Rules for array of filenames providing extended information .

Parameters:
ruleid - the ruleid e.g $$ecl or $$mrg
projectId - an IDE project identifier e.g "54321" - arbitrary string.
productId - optional product name.
worksetId - Project spec e.g PROD:ID.
projectRoot - the root of the project.
contextRoot - the context root (optional).
filenames - array of filenames to get details for
Returns:
an array of UploadItemDetails instances containing an ItemRevisionDetails instance for the following parameters for item creation or having the isAbleToUpload flag set to false and uploadErrorCode set if no rule found to upload or excluded. Note - project filename and userfilename are not filled in. $COMMENT $DESCRIPTION X $DIRPATH X $FILENAME $FORMAT $ITEM_ID $LIB_FILENAME $OWNING_PART_ID $OWNING_PART_PCS $OWNING_PART_VARIANT $PRODUCT_ID X $REVISION X $STATUS $TYPE $VARIANT $WSPATH
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if the ruleid, projectId, worksetId or projectRoot parameters are null.
DimensionsRuntimeException - if there was a general problem querying the rulesets.

runCommand

DimensionsResult runCommand(java.lang.String command)
Runs the Dimensions CM command line command specified in command. The command must be quoted and escaped as necessary. Note that not all commands can currently be run: for example, the commands upload and download cannot be used with this method.

Parameters:
command - the command.
Returns:
a DimensionsResult object on success.
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if the command does not succeed.
